# Adding a new grade (כיתה)

Use this checklist when introducing another workbook grade (e.g. ג׳) or changing how grades A/B work. Keep changes minimal; extend patterns rather than inventing parallel flows.

## How grades work today (mental model)

- **`GradeId`** lives in `lib/grades.ts`. It drives `parseGradeId` for `/grade/[grade]/*`, Hebrew labels (`gradeLabel`), and any `switch (grade)` branches.
- **Workbook content** is selected in `lib/content/workbook.ts`: grade A → `lib/content/days.ts`; grade B → `lib/content/days-grade-b.ts` (reuses `buildDayFromConcepts` / `DayConcept` from `days.ts`).
- **Plan / ministry UI** uses `getMinistryStrandsForGrade` and `getTotalCurriculumDaysForGrade` in `lib/content/curriculum-plan.ts` (length comes from the workbook for that grade).
- **Progress** is per grade in `lib/progress/storage.ts`: `kids_math.workbook_progress.v2.grade.${grade}`. Grade A has legacy migration from an older unscoped key; grade B had a v1 → v2 path—only add migrations if you introduce another predecessor key layout.
- **Final exam**: `FINAL_EXAM_DAY_ID` in `lib/final-exam/config.ts` is `day-29`.
- **Optional GMAT-style challenge**: after passing the final exam, learners can open `/grade/[grade]/gmat-challenge` (see `lib/gmat-challenge/*`, `components/screens/GmatChallengeScreen.tsx`). When adding a grade, run `pickGmatChallengeItems` + classifier against the new workbook or disable the CTA until pools validate. `components/screens/DayScreen.tsx` routes that id to `FinalExamScreen`. The exam **bank** and **localStorage** are per grade (`lib/final-exam/picker.ts`, `lib/final-exam/storage.ts`). After submit with pass ≥ `FINAL_EXAM_PASS_PERCENT`, **only grade `"a"`** triggers `POST /api/unlock-grade-b` (see `components/screens/FinalExamScreen.tsx`).
- **Grade B gate**: `middleware.ts` matches `/grade/b/:path*`. Without cookie `kids_math.unlocked_grade_b=1`, requests redirect to `app/grade/b/locked/page.tsx` (API paths under `/grade/b` are excluded so clients can still call unlock).
- **Grade picker**: `app/page.tsx`. **Legacy day URLs**: `app/day/[id]/page.tsx` is hardwired to grade **A** only.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  picker[GradePicker root]
  gradeHome["/grade/:grade"]
  mw{Middleware for grade b}
  locked["/grade/b/locked"]
  home[HomeScreen]
  day[DayScreen or FinalExam]
  progress["localStorage progress v2.grade.*"]
  examStore["localStorage final_exam v1.grade.*"]
  unlockApi["POST /api/unlock-grade-b"]
  picker --> gradeHome
  gradeHome --> mw
  mw -->|b no cookie| locked
  mw -->|a or b unlocked| home
  home --> day
  day --> progress
  day --> examStore
  examStore -->|pass on grade a| unlockApi
  unlockApi -->|Set-Cookie| mw
```

## Grade A vs grade B (reference)

| Area | Grade A | Grade B |
|------|---------|---------|
| Route gate | None | Middleware + valid unlock cookie |
| Content | `days.ts` | `days-grade-b.ts` + `workbook.ts` branch |
| Strands | `MINISTRY_STRANDS_GRADE_A` | `MINISTRY_STRANDS_GRADE_B` |
| Progress key | `v2.grade.a` (+ legacy migration) | `v2.grade.b` (+ optional v1 migration) |
| Unlock | N/A | Cookie after **A** final exam pass (85%+) |

## Implementation checklist (order matters)

1. **`lib/grades.ts`** — Extend `GradeId`, `parseGradeId`, `gradeLabel` (and `DEFAULT_GRADE` only if product requires).
2. **Content** — Add `lib/content/days-grade-*.ts` (or extend existing) and wire `getWorkbookDays` / `getWorkbookDaysById` in `lib/content/workbook.ts`.
3. **`lib/content/curriculum-plan.ts`** — Add strands constant + branch in `getMinistryStrandsForGrade`. If day numbers in strands must match the new workbook length, update them carefully.
4. **`lib/types.ts`** — New `SkillTag` values if the workbook needs tags not in the union; then exercise builders / warmup helpers that key off tags.
5. **Picker UI** — `app/page.tsx`: new card/link, analytics `grade_selected`, copy and `aria-label` if stale.
6. **Gated grade (optional)** — Mirror grade B: constants in `lib/gradeUnlock.ts`, `middleware.ts` `matcher` + redirect, `app/grade/<id>/locked/page.tsx`, `app/api/unlock-grade-<id>/route.ts`, and **exactly one** prerequisite final-exam success path that calls the unlock API (today: A → B). Ensure middleware still allows any API routes needed on that grade path.
7. **Progress** — Confirm new grade uses `v2.grade.${grade}` automatically; add targeted migration only if users already have data under a different key.
8. **Final exam** — Confirm last workbook day stays aligned with `FINAL_EXAM_DAY_ID` (today `day-29`). If length changes, centralize the id in config and replace hardcoded checks. Wire “unlock next grade” cookie only from the correct prerequisite grade’s `finishExam`.
9. **Admin tooling compatibility (required)** — New/changed grades must work with admin progress controls:
   - Grade picker entry to admin should remain available (`app/page.tsx` + `routes.adminProgress(...)`).
   - Per-grade admin actions in `components/screens/AdminProgressScreen.tsx` must support the grade:
     - mark single day complete/reset
     - mark all regular days complete
     - force final exam complete (enabled only after all regular days are complete)
   - `forceMarkDayComplete(..., { fillAnswers: true })` should keep prefilling answer state so reopening a completed day shows answers.
   - If your grade-unlock chain changes (e.g. B unlocks C), update admin forced-final-exam side effects consistently with the new prerequisite chain.
10. **Tests** — Use `tests/e2e/grade-b.spec.ts` as template for cookie gates; add unit tests if `parseGradeId` / storage gets new branches.
    - Add/update admin e2e coverage in `tests/e2e/admin-progress.spec.ts` for the new grade:
      - single-day complete/reset behavior
      - all-days-complete + final-exam-complete behavior
      - grade isolation (edits in one grade do not mutate another)
11. **Quality gates** — Run the required checks from `quality-gates.mdc` (risk-based matrix, including `check:testids`, `test:unit`, and `test:e2e` where applicable).

## Attention points (risks)

- **TypeScript exhaustiveness** — After extending `GradeId`, fix every `switch` / map until the compiler is clean.
- **Persisted data** — Avoid breaking `WorkbookProgressState` / final exam JSON shapes; prefer additive changes + version bumps with sanitizers if needed.
- **Middleware** — Do not block the unlock API or other required endpoints; grade B exempts `pathname.startsWith("/api/")` under `/grade/b`.
- **Product copy** — Picker text vs locked page vs final exam success message should stay consistent (e.g. grade B “בקרוב” vs actual gate).
- **Third gated grade** — Names like `unlock-grade-b` are B-specific; a chain A→B→C may need a generalized API or multiple narrow routes—plan before copying the pattern blindly.
- **Admin consistency** — If grade unlock prerequisites change, make sure admin forced-final-exam behavior triggers the same unlock side effects as the normal exam pass flow.
- **Educational content** — When adding real lesson text or progression, follow `multi-agent-playbook.mdc` / MoE verification expectations for syllabus alignment.

